{"lemma":"بِضْعٌ","slug":"بِضْعٌ","root":"ب.ض.ع","root_slug":"ب-ض-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ض-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بِضْع","root":"بضع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2701"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B6%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a few","examples":[{"text":"فِي بِضْعِ سِنِينَ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/bidˤʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2701","headword_ar":"بِضْعٌ","root":"bDE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baDoEN","text_ar":"بَضْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) some of the Arabs pronouncing it with kesr, (S, Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A number under ten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an odd number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number between two round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decimal, numbers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one to ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusive of the latter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from eleven to twenty"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exclusive of the latter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; so accord. to Mebremán; (K;) i. e. Mohammad Ibn-'Alee Ibn-Ismá'eel the Lexicologist, Mebremán being his surname: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to nine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K [in the first and last the ns. being in the fem. gender; but in the second, masc.];) so accord. to Katádeh; (Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to less than ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr [the ns. of number in the masc. gender]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not less than three nor more than ten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh [the first n. of number in the fem. gender, and the second masc.];)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh [the ns. of number in the masc. gender]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to seven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to five:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, K [the n. of number in the fem. gender]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one to four:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, O, K [the ns. of number in the masc. gender]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to five;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an explanation ascribed to AO: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from four to nine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K [the ns. of number fem.];) and this is the signification preferred by Th: (TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"five:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mukátil [this n. of number masc.]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mukátil, K [in the K this n. of number being fem.];) so accord. to some: (AO:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ed-Dahhák [this n. of number masc.]:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an undefined number;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayoru","text_ar":"غَيْرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHoduwdK","text_ar":"مَحْدُودٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so says Sgh; [and the like is said in the Msb;] in the K, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayoru maEoduwdK","text_ar":"غَيْرُ مَعْدُودٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) because it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K,) which is undefined: (Sgh, TA:) it also signifies,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with ten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ten and a number under ten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like: as]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thirteen to nineteen."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) When used as signifying from three to nine, (Mgh, Msb,) or to ten, or to seven, (Mgh,) [or to signify some number under ten, without another n. of number,] it is masc. and fem. without variation: (Mgh, Msb:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEu rijaAlK","text_ar":"بِضْعُ رِجَالٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From three to nine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEu nisowapK","text_ar":"بِضْعُ نِسْوَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to nine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEu siniyna","text_ar":"بِضْعُ سِنِينَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to nine"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY biDoEi siniyna","text_ar":"فِى بِضْعِ سِنِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in from three to nine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Kur xxx. 3:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falabiva fiY Als~ijoni biDoEa","text_ar":"فَلَبِثَ فِى السِّجْنِ بِضْعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siniyna","text_ar":"سِنِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he remained in the prison from three to nine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"years"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kur xii. 42.) But when used to denote a number above ten, (Mgh, Msb,) with a masc. n. it is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEap","text_ar":"بِضْعَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and with a fem. n. it is without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, Mgh, Msb, K:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEapa Ea$ara rajulFA","text_ar":"بِضْعَةَ عَشَرَ رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From thirteen to nineteen"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEa Ea$orapa A@moraA^apF","text_ar":"بِضْعَ عَشْرَةَ ا@مْرَاَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thirteen to nineteen"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, * TA:) like as you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapa Ea$ara rajulFA","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAva Ea$orpa A@moraA^apF","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَ عَشْرةَ ا@مْرَاَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) When you have passed the word denoting ten, (S, K,) [i. e.] to denote a number above twenty, (Msb,) it is not used: (S, Msb, K:) you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN waEi$oruwna","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ وَعِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nay~ifN waEi$oruwna","text_ar":"نَيِّفٌ وَعِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and so in the cases of the remaining numbers: (S:) or you do say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN waEi$oruwna","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ وَعِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh, K:) accord. to AZ, (Msb,) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEapN","text_ar":"بِضْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEi$oruwna rajulFA","text_ar":"وَعِشْرُونَ رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Twenty and odd men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN waEi$oruwna A@moraA^apF","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ وَعِشْرُونَ ا@مْرَاَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twenty and odd women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, TA:) but not the reverse: (K:) ISd says, we have not heard this, but there is no objection to it: (TA:) and Fr says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not mentioned save with ten and twenty to ninety; (IB, K;) not with what exceeds this: (IB:) you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN wamiAy^apN","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ وَمِايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN waA^alofN","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ وَاَلْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IB, K,) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miAy^apN","text_ar":"مِايَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wanay~ifN","text_ar":"وَنَيِّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alofN wanay~ifN","text_ar":"اَلْفٌ وَنَيِّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IB:) it occurs in trads. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei$oruwna","text_ar":"عِشْرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvuwna","text_ar":"ثَلَاثُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biDoEN","text_ar":"بِضْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baDoEN","text_ar":"بَضْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night: (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (Lh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY biDoEN mina All~ayoli","text_ar":"مَضَى بِضْعٌ مِنَ اللَّيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, of the night passed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) J mentions it with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and explains it by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawo$N","text_ar":"جَوْشٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","AO","Sgh","Mgh","ISk","AZ","IB"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}